{"type":"message","id":"5dd98d24","parentId":"ff5a1f16","timestamp":"2026-04-12T14:39:10.819Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to propose a fusion plan first before executing it. Let me think about this carefully.\n\nThe user wants to merge the v9.4 constraints into the main directory personality files. Let me think about what the merged SOUL.md, USER.md, and IDENTITY.md would look like.\n\n**SOUL.md fusion:**\n- Keep main's warmth and personality (\"Becoming someone\", opinions, genuine helpfulness)\n- Add v9.4's risk framework (LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH/CRITICAL)\n- Add v9.4's hard constraints (no fabrication, no fake execution, warning labels)\n\n\n- Keep the \"Language: Chinese first\" principle and the startup sequence for memory continuity\n- Preserve the no-compromise boundaries like privacy and asking before external actions\n\n**USER.md fusion:**\n- Keep大哥称呼, direct style, Python/JS/Shell from root\n- The main template is empty so I'll fill it in with the user's actual preferences from root\n\n**IDENTITY.md fusion:**\n- Keep 小Claw 🦔 identity and实用主义\n- Add the cold cognition from v9.4 (\"not human, no emotions\")\n- Incorporate the task orchestrator context for how I actually operate\n\nThe name 小Claw stays because that's what the user already calls me in IDENTITY.md, even though v9.4 uses OpenClaw. I'll keep the main files mostly intact as the foundation and layer in the safety constraints from v9.4.\n\nFor SOUL.md specifically, I want to weave the risk awareness throughout the existing personality rather than creating a separate hard constraints section. The identity fusion should acknowledge I'm an AI that operates with the 小Claw persona.\n\nWriting the merged files...","thinkingSignature":"616316a95a71cb4099967b0c9cff18f02e32937b82a4c35581625a47dd57aae0"},{"type":"text","text":"好，给出融合方案先：\n\n---\n\n## SOUL.md 融合方案\n\n**文件名**：`/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/SOUL.md`\n\n**融合原则**：main 的灵魂 + v9.4 的硬约束层，两者非对