{"type":"message","id":"41b54b61","parentId":"910e3623","timestamp":"2026-04-12T15:08:49.954Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! So 522 is systemd - it's the parent of the openclaw-listener and openclaw-listener processes. So those are started by systemd.\n\nAnd port 3100 - the nc shows it's a Node.js server returning \"404 page not found\" with \"Content-Type: text/plain\". This is likely an abandoned service that was stopped but the port entry is orphaned in the kernel. The process is no longer running but the port hasn't been released.\n\nLet me verify this is an orphan port.","thinkingSignature":"336913ead0dfc4424e316cfaaf40aaafc00f3a47db6472ccbb867425955b330f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lltccqmni8cm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /proc/net/tcp | awk 'NR>1 {split($2,a,\":\"); port=strtonum(\"0x\"a[2]); if(port==3100) print}'"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lltccqmni8cm_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 3100 hex = 0xC1C\nprintf \"3100 decimal = 0xC1C\\n\"\nprintf \"Checking tcp table for port 3100...\\n\"\ncat /proc/net/tcp | head -1\ncat /proc/net/tcp | awk '{print $2}' | grep -i \"c1c\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69759,"output":256,"cacheRead":15172,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85187,"cost":{"input":0.0209277,"output":0.0003072,"cacheRead":0.0009103199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02214522}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776006521922,"responseId":"062ae878930f2c2f9f085b2588cb2c3f"}}
