{"type":"message","id":"4cfffa78","parentId":"3fbd1739","timestamp":"2026-04-12T15:08:57.322Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - when I grep for \"c1c\" (the hex representation of 3100), I don't find any matches in /proc/net/tcp. But the port IS listening according to ss. This is very strange.Wait - 3100 = 0xC1C but port numbers in /proc/net/tcp are in big-endian hex. Let me check the hex more carefully.\n\nActually wait - ss shows the port is listening but there's no process attached to it. And /proc/net/tcp doesn't show it either (when filtering for port 3100). Let me check if maybe it's IPv6.","thinkingSignature":"d1fa863de7f95b31fd32740eeac9b79347fbf927fe0fa9e172f4e01fd829a298"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_utra64nxsivc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /proc/net/tcp6 | head -3; echo \"---\"; cat /proc/net/tcp6 | awk '{print $2}' | grep -i \"c1c\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_utra64nxsivc_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp | grep 3100; echo \"---\"; cat /proc/net/tcp | wc -l; cat /proc/net/tcp6 | wc -l"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":70087,"output":244,"cacheRead":15172,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85503,"cost":{"input":0.0210261,"output":0.00029279999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0009103199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.022229219999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776006530058,"responseId":"062ae882be5603afedcb22f2d95f1fee"}}
