{"type":"message","id":"24453c94","parentId":"9caec249","timestamp":"2026-04-12T16:51:52.012Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to study the v8-core document more carefully, and then improve the v8_scorer and v8_classifier skills based on what I learned. Let me think about what the document actually provides vs what I wrote.\n\nMy current v8_scorer SKILL.md just has basic API docs. The document's v8-core has:\n1. A complete IntentClassifier with embedding + keyword fallback\n2. A ComplexityScorer with rule-based + ML model\n3. A StrategyRouter with proper threshold logic\n4. A scenarios.json with rich training data\n5. config.yaml with all parameters\n\nMy v8_classifier just calls /classify on 3104 and returns scene/confidence. But the document's classifier is more sophisticated - it has:\n- 7 scene types with rich examples\n\n\n- cosine similarity scoring\n- LRU cache\n- jieba tokenization\n\nNow I need to figure out how much of this actually matches what's running on 3103 and 3104. The document describes a sophisticated architecture, but our current 3104 classifier might be running something simpler. I should examine the actual 3104 implementation to understand the gap between what I documented and what's really running, then reassess whether my skills need to be rewritten or if the underlying system itself needs upgrading.\n\nThe real issue is that my v8_scorer and v8_classifier are just thin wrappers around the APIs—I documented the endpoints but missed the actual intelligence. The v8-core proposal has real complexity with scoring models and routing logic, but it lives on port 3003 which doesn't exist yet, while the actual services we have are running on different ports with potentially different implementations.","thinkingSignature":"b4154d6746ec54e516c520d437b6ff6ef0ce1b0ff35a1fcc37490fced63d3134"},{"type":"text","text":"你说得对，我那两个 skill 就是 API 文档抄了一遍，没有承载任何真正的理解。让我好好学一下方案，再重新看现有的：\n"},{"type":"toolCall",