{"type":"message","id":"baa64e50","parentId":"0e1ca2d1","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:06:17.774Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see several issues:\n\n1. **Port 3100** - still a zombie/orphan port (no process, kernel-held)\n2. **3103 intent endpoint** - returns 404, doesn't exist. The skill says there's `/api/intent` but it doesn't actually exist. The scoring.js exports `detectIntent` but the API server doesn't expose it as a route.\n3. **Skills 目录不一致** - `~/.openclaw/skills/` 只有3个（claude-code-codingplan, self-improving-agent, task_orchestrator），而 `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` 有22个。说明 workspace 的 skill 没有同步到 ~/.openclaw/skills/。\n\nWait - the diff output shows the LEFT column (1,2c1,22) has fewer items, and the RIGHT column has more. \n\nSo `~/.openclaw/skills/` has fewer skills than `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/`. The 3103 API doesn't have the `/api/intent` endpoint even though the skill documents it - that's a discrepancy. The 3104 classify endpoint is returning `\"intercepted\":false` which looks correct, but it's oddly returning a warning message in the `[LLM响应]` field.\n\nLooking at the `intercepted` field more carefully, it says `false` yet there's a `[!WARNING]` in the response, which seems contradictory. The 3104 is functioning but with this odd LLM-generated warning attached. Let me verify the skill documents and other systems are still working properly.","thinkingSignature":"a4ff22408dd554421001031c5c4dedf42afa89024b4be5b908d5d4047c88fca1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f164gelmmvqe_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Skills 双向同步检查 ===\" && for f in ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/*/SKILL.md; do name=$(basename $(dirname $f)); dest=\"$HOME/.openclaw/skills/$name/SKILL.md\"; if [ -f \"$dest\" ]; then diff \"$f\" \"$dest\" > /dev/null 2>&1 && echo \"✓ $name\" || echo \"✗ $name (不同步)\"; else echo \"? $name (目标不存在)\"; fi; done"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f164gelmmvqe_2","name":"exe