{"type":"message","id":"bdf1ea53","parentId":"d18da6d8","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:12:33.351Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both skill directories exist with their full structure. They're set up but I need to understand how to \"activate\" them in the current session context.\n\nIn OpenClaw, workspace skills are loaded from the workspace skills directory. But in the system prompt, the `available_skills` list shows the system-level skills. The workspace skills should be available if the workspace is set correctly.\n\nLet me check if the current session's workspace is correctly configured, and whether I can use the skill loading mechanism.\n\nActually, looking at the system prompt's \"Skills\" section, it says:\n\"Skills provide your tools. When you need one, check its SKILL.md. Keep local notes (camera names, SSH details, voice preferences) in TOOLS.md.\"\n\n\nSo skills are loaded on-demand from their SKILL.md files rather than being pre-activated. Since the workspace is `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main` and the skills directory is at `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/`, they should be discoverable when I reference them. I should verify the workspace configuration is pointing to the right location.","thinkingSignature":"7bcd23d4d9c6602e9e2b59c6266992cf2b57ae26dda42e9f98f3546d45ff0c8a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2bzmbyeyjcrn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"self-improving:\" && cat ~/self-improving/memory.md 2>/dev/null | head -20; echo; echo \"proactivity:\" && cat ~/proactivity/memory.md 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109724,"output":300,"cacheRead":15172,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125196,"cost":{"input":0.0329172,"output":0.00035999999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0009103199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03418752}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776013946873,"responseId":"062b057ab41ac683cc79a5975ea9edd