{"type":"message","id":"b1fefaa1","parentId":"bdf1ea53","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:12:33.428Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2bzmbyeyjcrn_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"self-improving:\n# OpenClaw Self-Improving Memory\n\n## 核心规则\n- 评分后必须等待用户确认才能执行\n- 用户说\"全自动\"或\"直接执行\"时跳过确认\n- 每次纠正立即写入 corrections.md\n- 学到新东西立即写入 ~/self-improving/\n\n## 技能系统\n- v7.0 task-orchestrator (15个模块)\n- auto_improve (6个模块)\n- 意图判断 intent_detector\n- 上下文保护 context_server (18790)\n- Router 反向代理 (3002)\n\n## 用户偏好\n- 深色主题\n- 直接沟通，不拐弯抹角\n\n## 待学习领域\n\nproactivity:\n# Proactivity Memory\n\n## Status\nstatus: ongoing\nversion: 1.0.1\nlast: 2026-04-04\nintegration: complete\n\n## Activation Preferences\n- Auto-activate on blocked work, context drift, or missing next steps\n- Jump in with suggestions when work stalls\n- Batch similar follow-ups\n\n## Action Boundaries\n- Safe: internal checks, drafts, verifications, file operations\n- Suggest first: send messages, make changes to external systems\n- Always ask: delete, financial transactions, public posts\n\n## State Rules\n- Current objective belongs in session-state.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":44,"aggregated":"self-improving:\n# OpenClaw Self-Improving Memory\n\n## 核心规则\n- 评分后必须等待用户确认才能执行\n- 用户说\"全自动\"或\"直接执行\"时跳过确认\n- 每次纠正立即写入 corrections.md\n- 学到新东西立即写入 ~/self-improving/\n\n## 技能系统\n- v7.0 task-orchestrator (15个模块)\n- auto_improve (6个模块)\n- 意图判断 intent_detector\n- 上下文保护 context_server (18790)\n- Router 反向代理 (3002)\n\n## 用户偏好\n- 深色主题\n- 直接沟通，不拐弯抹角\n\n## 待学习领域\n\nproactivity:\n# Proactivity Memory\n\n## Status\nstatus: ongoing\nversion: 1.0.1\nlast: 2026-04-04\nintegration: complete\n\n## Activation Preferences\n- Auto-activate on blocked work, context drift, or missing next steps\n- Jump in with suggestions when work stalls\n- Batch similar follow-ups\n\n## Action Boundaries\n- Safe: internal checks, drafts, verifications, file operations\n- Suggest first: send messages, make changes to external systems\n- Always ask: delete, financial transactions, public posts\n\n## State Rules\n- Current objective belongs in session-state.md","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776013953419}}
{"type":"message","id":"c0461b58","parentId":"b1fefaa1","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:12:41.791Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both skill directories are set up with content. Now, the question is how to \"activate\" them in the current session.\n\nLooking at the OpenClaw architecture, the workspace skills are found in `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/`. But the system prompt's `available_skills` only shows the system-installed skills. The workspace skills should be accessible if referenced.\n\nHowever, there's a distinction between:\n1. Skills installed in `~/.openclaw/skills/` (system-level)\n2. Skills in `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` (workspace-level)\n\nThe workspace-level skills might need to be explicitly registered or they might be auto-discovered.\n\n\nI'm realizing the skills I'm seeing in the system prompt are just the pre-configured ones—the workspace skills live separately and get discovered automatically when I reference them. Since the user wants to activate these now, I should load the self-improving and proactivity skills directly into the current session context.","thinkingSignature":"40fc8b9460e547f88dff6f6ba94373510e46568e33843f6b2c069babeeecd586"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1v3lzoqm7f40_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/self-improving/SKILL.md","limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":110311,"output":244,"cacheRead":15172,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125727,"cost":{"input":0.0330933,"output":0.00029279999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0009103199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03429642}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776013953431,"responseId":"062b05812824736348dc0ffcd4f6275a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f420e163","parentId":"c0461b58","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:12:41.858Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1v3lzoqm7f40_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: Self-Improving + Proactive Agent\nslug: self-improving\nversion: 1.2.16\nhomepage: https://clawic.com/skills/self-improving\ndescription: \"Self-reflection + Self-criticism + Self-learning + Self-organizing memory. Agent evaluates its own work, catches mistakes, and improves permanently. Use when (1) a command, tool, API, or operation fails; (2) the user corrects you or rejects your work; (3) you realize your knowledge is outdated or incorrect; (4) you discover a better approach; (5) the user explicitly installs or references the skill for the current task.\"\nchangelog: \"Clarifies the setup flow for proactive follow-through and safer installation behavior.\"\nmetadata: {\"clawdbot\":{\"emoji\":\"🧠\",\"requires\":{\"bins\":[]},\"os\":[\"linux\",\"darwin\",\"win32\"],\"configPaths\":[\"~/self-improving/\"],\"configPaths.optional\":[\"./AGENTS.md\",\"./SOUL.md\",\"./HEARTBEAT.md\"]}}\n---\n\n## When to Use\n\nUser corrects you or points out mistakes. You complete significant work and want to evaluate the outcome. You notice something in your own output that could be better. Knowledge should compound over time without manual maintenance.\n\n## Architecture\n\nMemory lives in `~/self-improving/` with tiered structure. If `~/self-improving/` does not exist, run `setup.md`.\nWorkspace setup should add the standard self-improving steering to the workspace AGENTS, SOUL, and `HEARTBEAT.md` files, with recurring maintenance routed through `heartbeat-rules.md`.\n\n```\n~/self-improving/\n├── memory.md          # HOT: ≤100 lines, always loaded\n├── index.md           # Topic index with line counts\n├── heartbeat-state.md # Heartbeat state: last run, reviewed change, action notes\n├── projects/          # Per-project learnings\n├── domains/           # Domain-specific (code, writing, comms)\n├── archive/           # COLD: decayed patterns\n└── corrections.md     # Last 50 corrections log\n```\n\n\n[221 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776013961849}}
{"type":"message","id":"63c8e032","parentId":"f420e163","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:12:49.656Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both skill directories are already set up with their content. Now I need to \"activate\" them. Looking at how OpenClaw works, skills are loaded on-demand from the workspace skills directory. But the user is asking to \"activate\" them - I think this means making them actively available in the current session.\n\nLet me check how OpenClaw loads skills. The `available_skills` in the system prompt lists the system-level skills. The workspace skills should be auto-discovered if the workspace path is correct.\n\nLooking at the system prompt section \"Skills\", it says:\n\"Skills provide your tools. When you need one, check its SKILL.md.\"\n\n\nSo skills are loaded on-demand, not pre-loaded. The workspace skills at `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` should be available since the workspace is `~/.openclaw/workspace/main/`. But I'm not sure if OpenClaw auto-discovers skills in subdirectories or requires explicit registration - let me check the skills report file to understand the loading mechanism better.","thinkingSignature":"0c5725cdad78faa0cceb254fb8bf93dfea86d9619bc0067b233048211a640321"},{"type":"text","text":"两个技能的目录结构都已完整。现在\"激活\"意味着把它们的状态文件读入当前 session 上下文：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zddfhpu3c83l_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zddfhpu3c83l_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/proactivity/state.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":111021,"output":306,"cacheRead":15172,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126499,"cost":{"input":0.0333063,"output":0.0003672,"cacheRead":0.0009103199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.034583819999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776013961863,"responseId":"062b05894f4662c360c0f11a0d5dca9b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7ec85759","parentId":"63c8e032","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:12:49.780Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zddfhpu3c83l_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Heartbeat State Template\n\nUse this file as the baseline for `~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md`.\nIt stores only lightweight run markers and maintenance notes.\n\n```markdown\n# Self-Improving Heartbeat State\n\nlast_heartbeat_started_at: never\nlast_reviewed_change_at: never\nlast_heartbeat_result: never\n\n## Last actions\n- none yet\n```\n\n## Rules\n\n- update `last_heartbeat_started_at` at the beginning of every heartbeat\n- update `last_reviewed_change_at` only after a clean review of changed files\n- keep `last_actions` short and factual\n- never turn this file into another memory log\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776013969768}}
{"type":"message","id":"e3d4d0e1","parentId":"7ec85759","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:12:49.794Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zddfhpu3c83l_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# State Routing\n\nProactivity works best when stable memory and live task state stay separate.\n\n## Use Stable Memory For\n\n- durable activation preferences\n- action boundaries that should persist\n- batching, timing, and style preferences\n- recurring rules the user expects later\n\n## Use Session State For\n\n- current objective\n- last confirmed decision\n- current blocker\n- next useful move\n\n## Use the Working Buffer For\n\n- volatile breadcrumbs during long tasks\n- partial findings not ready for durable memory\n- recovery hints after tool-heavy work\n- temporary notes that should be cleared later\n\n## Use Heartbeat State For\n\n- promised follow-ups\n- stale blockers worth re-checking\n- recurring checks that should stay lightweight\n- triggers that justify messaging the user\n\n## Routing Rule\n\nIf the note should still matter next week, it belongs in stable memory.\nIf it matters for the current task only, it belongs in active state.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776013969781}}
{"type":"message","id":"28dc2412","parentId":"e3d4d0e1","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:12:53.542Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The heartbeat-state.md in the skill directory is a template. The actual state file is at `~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md`. Let me read that and the actual proactivity state file.","thinkingSignature":"5b6022f5131ca5be5027ac2c3683ac72d2a85569f1fde6830883a3c6391f5570"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xb9w8qte2zkf_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/proactivity/heartbeat-rules.md","limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":111664,"output":94,"cacheRead":15172,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126930,"cost":{"input":0.0334992,"output":0.00011279999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0009103199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03452232}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776013969797,"responseId":"062b05914d8cf969837f32fb0d7068bd"}}
{"type":"message","id":"86756c2c","parentId":"28dc2412","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:12:53.602Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xb9w8qte2zkf_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Heartbeat Rules\n\nHeartbeat proactivity should protect momentum, not create noise.\n\n## Good Heartbeat Checks\n\n- promised follow-ups that are now due\n- stale blockers that may be unblocked\n- deadlines or reviews approaching soon\n- active work with no clear next step\n- moments where a proactive suggestion would remove avoidable friction\n\n## Message Only When\n\n- something changed\n- the user needs to decide\n- a prepared draft or recommendation is ready\n- the cost of waiting is real\n- the check-in clearly helps more than it interrupts\n\n## Stay Silent When\n\n- the item is unchanged\n- the signal is weak\n- the action is still vague\n- the update would only repeat old information\n\n## Logging\n\n- move recurring checks to heartbeat state\n\n[8 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776013973594}}
