{"type":"message","id":"e7555d8e","parentId":"f80cf2f5","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:18:33.476Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_muvq9e1htp03_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"22099 ⭐  volcengine/OpenViking\n         OpenViking is an open-source context database designed specifically for AI Agents(such as openclaw). OpenViking unifies the management of context (memory, resources, and skills) that Agents need through a file system paradigm, enabling hierarchical context delivery and self-evolving.\n\n9075 ⭐  activeloopai/deeplake\n         Deeplake is AI Data Runtime for Agents. It provides serverless postgres with a multimodal datalake, enabling scalable retrieval and training.\n\n8314 ⭐  MemTensor/MemOS\n         AI memory OS for LLM and Agent systems(moltbot,clawdbot,openclaw), enabling persistent Skill memory for cross-task skill reuse and evolution.\n\n 611 ⭐  alvinreal/awesome-openclaw\n         A curated list of the best OpenClaw resources: official projects, skills, plugins, dashboards, deployment tooling, memory systems, and guides.\n\n 370 ⭐  freddy-schuetz/n8n-claw\n         OpenClaw-inspired autonomous AI agent built entirely in n8n. Adaptive RAG-powered memory, Skills via MCP templates, Expert Agents with delegated sub-agents, proactive task management, media understanding - self-hosted with one setup script\n\n 320 ⭐  swarmclawai/swarmclaw\n         Build and run autonomous AI agents with OpenClaw, Hermes, multiple model providers, orchestration, delegation, memory, skills, schedules, and chat connectors.\n\n 265 ⭐  win4r/openclaw-workspace\n         Claude Code skill for maintaining and optimizing OpenClaw workspace files (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md, checklists)\n\n 257 ⭐  sopaco/cortex-mem\n         🧠 The production-ready cognitive foundation for autonomous systems such as OpenClaw and Embodied-AI. For memory management, from extraction and search to automated optimization, with SKILL, CLI, API, MCP, and insights dashboard out-of-the-box.\n\n 246 ⭐  zhimaAi/ChatClaw\n         ChatClaw: Get OpenClaw-like knowledge base personal AI agent in 5 mins. Sandbox-secured, ultra-small 30MB installer for macOS & Windows (install in 1 min). Connects to WhatsApp, Telegram, Slack, Discord, Gmail, DingTalk, WeChat Work, QQ, Feishu. Built-in Skill Market, Knowledge Base, Memory, MCP, Scheduled Tasks. Developed in Go ,run\n\n 222 ⭐  CortexReach/memory-lancedb-pro-skill\n         Claude Code skill for memory-lancedb-pro — production-grade long-term memory plugin for OpenClaw"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1103,"aggregated":"22099 ⭐  volcengine/OpenViking\n         OpenViking is an open-source context database designed specifically for AI Agents(such as openclaw). OpenViking unifies the management of context (memory, resources, and skills) that Agents need through a file system paradigm, enabling hierarchical context delivery and self-evolving.\n\n9075 ⭐  activeloopai/deeplake\n         Deeplake is AI Data Runtime for Agents. It provides serverless postgres with a multimodal datalake, enabling scalable retrieval and training.\n\n8314 ⭐  MemTensor/MemOS\n         AI memory OS for LLM and Agent systems(moltbot,clawdbot,openclaw), enabling persistent Skill memory for cross-task skill reuse and evolution.\n\n 611 ⭐  alvinreal/awesome-openclaw\n         A curated list of the best OpenClaw resources: official projects, skills, plugins, dashboards, deployment tooling, memory systems, and guides.\n\n 370 ⭐  freddy-schuetz/n8n-claw\n         OpenClaw-inspired autonomous AI agent built entirely in n8n. Adaptive RAG-powered memory, Skills via MCP templates, Expert Agents with delegated sub-agents, proactive task management, media understanding - self-hosted with one setup script\n\n 320 ⭐  swarmclawai/swarmclaw\n         Build and run autonomous AI agents with OpenClaw, Hermes, multiple model providers, orchestration, delegation, memory, skills, schedules, and chat connectors.\n\n 265 ⭐  win4r/openclaw-workspace\n         Claude Code skill for maintaining and optimizing OpenClaw workspace files (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md, checklists)\n\n 257 ⭐  sopaco/cortex-mem\n         🧠 The production-ready cognitive foundation for autonomous systems such as OpenClaw and Embodied-AI. For memory management, from extraction and search to automated optimization, with SKILL, CLI, API, MCP, and insights dashboard out-of-the-box.\n\n 246 ⭐  zhimaAi/ChatClaw\n         ChatClaw: Get OpenClaw-like knowledge base personal AI agent in 5 mins. Sandbox-secured, ultra-small 30MB installer for macOS & Windows (install in 1 min). Connects to WhatsApp, Telegram, Slack, Discord, Gmail, DingTalk, WeChat Work, QQ, Feishu. Built-in Skill Market, Knowledge Base, Memory, MCP, Scheduled Tasks. Developed in Go ,run\n\n 222 ⭐  CortexReach/memory-lancedb-pro-skill\n         Claude Code skill for memory-lancedb-pro — production-grade long-term memory plugin for OpenClaw","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776014313467}}
{"type":"message","id":"304c3d7b","parentId":"e7555d8e","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:18:45.021Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Very interesting findings from GitHub! Let me highlight the most relevant ones for memory and context:\n\n1. **volcengine/OpenViking** (22099 ⭐) - OpenViking is an open-source **context database** designed specifically for AI Agents (such as openclaw). It unifies memory, resources, and skills management through a file system paradigm. This seems like the most relevant for context/memory.\n\n2. **MemTensor/MemOS** (9075 ⭐) - AI memory OS for LLM and Agent systems (moltbot, clawdbot, openclaw), enabling persistent Skill memory for cross-task skill reuse and evolution.\n\n\n3. **sopaco/cortex-mem** (257 ⭐) - A production-ready cognitive foundation for autonomous systems like OpenClaw that handles the full memory lifecycle from extraction and search to optimization, with SKILL, CLI, API, MCP, and dashboard capabilities out-of-the-box. I should also check awesome-openclaw for broader context on what's available, and **win4r/openclaw-workspace** (265 ⭐) which appears to be a workspace management skill that could be relevant here.\n\nThe most compelling options are **cortex-mem** for production-ready memory with MCP integration and dashboard, **OpenViking** for a dedicated context database, **MemOS** for persistent skill memory, and **memory-lancedb-pro-skill** for LanceDB vector search capabilities. I should prioritize these based on what fits the existing architecture.","thinkingSignature":"4daeeb130a8dd78338ea109463f2a325de66c9433a31b320807e3026eb271838"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d7uetsoamv1y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=openclaw+memory+OR+context+skill&sort=stars&per_page=20\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor r in data.get('items', []):\n    print(f\\\"{r['stargazers_count']:>5}  {r['full_name']}\\\")\n    print(f\\\"         {r['description'] or 'N/A'}\\\")\n    print()\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":114825,"output":444,"cacheRead":15172,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130441,"cost":{"input":0.0344475,"output":0.0005327999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0009103199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03589062}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776014313479,"responseId":"062b06e95825c8a054c95b5bb5ad5be4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b101d3e","parentId":"304c3d7b","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:18:46.402Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d7uetsoamv1y_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"45710  VoltAgent/awesome-openclaw-skills\n         The awesome collection of OpenClaw skills. 5,400+ skills filtered and categorized from the official OpenClaw Skills Registry.🦞\n\n43002  zhayujie/CowAgent\n         CowAgent (chatgpt-on-wechat) 是基于大模型的超级AI助理，能主动思考和任务规划、访问操作系统和外部资源、创造和执行Skills、通过长期记忆和知识库不断成长，比OpenClaw更轻量和便捷。同时支持微信、飞书、钉钉、企微、QQ、公众号、网页等接入，可选择OpenAI/Claude/Gemini/DeepSeek/ Qwen/GLM/Kimi/LinkAI，能处理文本、语音、图片和文件，可快速搭建个人AI助理和企业数字员工。\n\n23236  safishamsi/graphify\n         AI coding assistant skill (Claude Code, Codex, OpenCode, Cursor, Gemini CLI, OpenClaw, Factory Droid, Trae). Turn any folder of code, docs, papers, images, videos, or YouTube links into a queryable knowledge graph\n\n23100  kepano/obsidian-skills\n         Agent skills for Obsidian. Teach your agent to use Markdown, Bases, JSON Canvas, and use the CLI.\n\n22099  volcengine/OpenViking\n         OpenViking is an open-source context database designed specifically for AI Agents(such as openclaw). OpenViking unifies the management of context (memory, resources, and skills) that Agents need through a file system paradigm, enabling hierarchical context delivery and self-evolving.\n\n20900  mvanhorn/last30days-skill\n         AI agent skill that researches any topic across Reddit, X, YouTube, HN, Polymarket, and the web - then synthesizes a grounded summary\n\n11710  liyupi/ai-guide\n         程序员鱼皮的 AI 资源大全 + Vibe Coding 零基础教程，分享 OpenClaw 保姆级教程、大模型玩法（DeepSeek / GPT / Gemini / Claude）、最新 AI 资讯、Prompt 提示词大全、AI 知识百科（Agent Skills / RAG / MCP / A2A）、AI 编程教程、AI 工具用法（Cursor / Claude Code / TRAE / Lovable / Copilot）、AI 开发框架教程（Spring AI / LangChain）、AI 产品变现指南，帮你快速掌握 AI 技术，走在时代前沿。本项目为开源文档，已升级为鱼皮 AI 导航网站\n\n10661  alirezarezvani/claude-skills\n         232+ Claude Code skills & agent plugins for Claude Code, Codex, Gemini CLI, Cursor, and 8 more coding agents — engineering, marketing, product, compliance, C-level advisory.\n\n10288  teng-lin/notebooklm-py\n         Unofficial Python API and agentic skill for Google NotebookLM. Full programmatic access to NotebookLM's features—including capabilities the web UI doesn't expose—via Python, CLI, and AI agents like Claude Code, Codex, and OpenClaw.\n\n 9075  activeloopai/deeplake\n         Deeplake is AI Data Runtime for Agents. It provides serverless postgres with a multimodal datalake, enabling scalable retrieval and training.\n\n 8314  MemTensor/MemOS\n         AI memory OS for LLM and Agent systems(moltbot,clawdbot,openclaw), enabling persistent Skill memory for cross-task skill reuse and evolution.\n\n 7891  openclaw/clawhub\n         Skill Directory for OpenClaw\n\n 6444  ValueCell-ai/ClawX\n         ClawX is a desktop app that provides a graphical interface for OpenClaw AI agents. It turns CLI-based AI orchestration into a desktop experience without using the terminal. China website is https://clawx.com.cn.\n\n 6285  wanshuiyin/Auto-claude-code-research-in-sleep\n         ARIS ⚔️ (Auto-Research-In-Sleep) — Lightweight Markdown-only skills for autonomous ML research: cross-model review loops, idea discovery, and experiment automation. No framework, no lock-in — works with Claude Code, Codex, OpenClaw, or any LLM agent.\n\n 4043  openclaw/skills\n         All versions of all skills that are on clawhub.com archived\n\n 4014  libukai/awesome-agent-skills\n         Agent Skills 终极指南：快速入门、资源推荐、精选技能与实用工具 ｜The Ultimate Guide to Agent Skills: QuickStart, Resources, Features&Toolkit\n\n 3894  clawdbot-ai/awesome-openclaw-skills-zh\n         OpenClaw 中文官方技能库 | 翻译自 Clawdbot 官方技能，按场景分类整理，支持中文自然语言调用\n\n 3438  Tencent/AI-Infra-Guard\n         A full-stack AI Red Teaming platform securing AI ecosystems via OpenClaw Security Scan, Agent Scan, Skills Scan, MCP scan, AI Infra scan and LLM jailbreak evaluation.\n\n 2733  davepoon/buildwithclaude\n         A single hub to find Claude Skills, Agents, Commands, Hooks, Plugins, and Marketplace collections to extend Claude Code, Claude Desktop, Agent SDK and OpenClaw\n\n 2513  white0dew/XiaohongshuSkills\n         支持小红书自动发布、自动评论、自动检索的 Skill。支持 OpenClaw、Codex、CC 等"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1350,"aggregated":"45710  VoltAgent/awesome-openclaw-skills\n         The awesome collection of OpenClaw skills. 5,400+ skills filtered and categorized from the official OpenClaw Skills Registry.🦞\n\n43002  zhayujie/CowAgent\n         CowAgent (chatgpt-on-wechat) 是基于大模型的超级AI助理，能主动思考和任务规划、访问操作系统和外部资源、创造和执行Skills、通过长期记忆和知识库不断成长，比OpenClaw更轻量和便捷。同时支持微信、飞书、钉钉、企微、QQ、公众号、网页等接入，可选择OpenAI/Claude/Gemini/DeepSeek/ Qwen/GLM/Kimi/LinkAI，能处理文本、语音、图片和文件，可快速搭建个人AI助理和企业数字员工。\n\n23236  safishamsi/graphify\n         AI coding assistant skill (Claude Code, Codex, OpenCode, Cursor, Gemini CLI, OpenClaw, Factory Droid, Trae). Turn any folder of code, docs, papers, images, videos, or YouTube links into a queryable knowledge graph\n\n23100  kepano/obsidian-skills\n         Agent skills for Obsidian. Teach your agent to use Markdown, Bases, JSON Canvas, and use the CLI.\n\n22099  volcengine/OpenViking\n         OpenViking is an open-source context database designed specifically for AI Agents(such as openclaw). OpenViking unifies the management of context (memory, resources, and skills) that Agents need through a file system paradigm, enabling hierarchical context delivery and self-evolving.\n\n20900  mvanhorn/last30days-skill\n         AI agent skill that researches any topic across Reddit, X, YouTube, HN, Polymarket, and the web - then synthesizes a grounded summary\n\n11710  liyupi/ai-guide\n         程序员鱼皮的 AI 资源大全 + Vibe Coding 零基础教程，分享 OpenClaw 保姆级教程、大模型玩法（DeepSeek / GPT / Gemini / Claude）、最新 AI 资讯、Prompt 提示词大全、AI 知识百科（Agent Skills / RAG / MCP / A2A）、AI 编程教程、AI 工具用法（Cursor / Claude Code / TRAE / Lovable / Copilot）、AI 开发框架教程（Spring AI / LangChain）、AI 产品变现指南，帮你快速掌握 AI 技术，走在时代前沿。本项目为开源文档，已升级为鱼皮 AI 导航网站\n\n10661  alirezarezvani/claude-skills\n         232+ Claude Code skills & agent plugins for Claude Code, Codex, Gemini CLI, Cursor, and 8 more coding agents — engineering, marketing, product, compliance, C-level advisory.\n\n10288  teng-lin/notebooklm-py\n         Unofficial Python API and agentic skill for Google NotebookLM. Full programmatic access to NotebookLM's features—including capabilities the web UI doesn't expose—via Python, CLI, and AI agents like Claude Code, Codex, and OpenClaw.\n\n 9075  activeloopai/deeplake\n         Deeplake is AI Data Runtime for Agents. It provides serverless postgres with a multimodal datalake, enabling scalable retrieval and training.\n\n 8314  MemTensor/MemOS\n         AI memory OS for LLM and Agent systems(moltbot,clawdbot,openclaw), enabling persistent Skill memory for cross-task skill reuse and evolution.\n\n 7891  openclaw/clawhub\n         Skill Directory for OpenClaw\n\n 6444  ValueCell-ai/ClawX\n         ClawX is a desktop app that provides a graphical interface for OpenClaw AI agents. It turns CLI-based AI orchestration into a desktop experience without using the terminal. China website is https://clawx.com.cn.\n\n 6285  wanshuiyin/Auto-claude-code-research-in-sleep\n         ARIS ⚔️ (Auto-Research-In-Sleep) — Lightweight Markdown-only skills for autonomous ML research: cross-model review loops, idea discovery, and experiment automation. No framework, no lock-in — works with Claude Code, Codex, OpenClaw, or any LLM agent.\n\n 4043  openclaw/skills\n         All versions of all skills that are on clawhub.com archived\n\n 4014  libukai/awesome-agent-skills\n         Agent Skills 终极指南：快速入门、资源推荐、精选技能与实用工具 ｜The Ultimate Guide to Agent Skills: QuickStart, Resources, Features&Toolkit\n\n 3894  clawdbot-ai/awesome-openclaw-skills-zh\n         OpenClaw 中文官方技能库 | 翻译自 Clawdbot 官方技能，按场景分类整理，支持中文自然语言调用\n\n 3438  Tencent/AI-Infra-Guard\n         A full-stack AI Red Teaming platform securing AI ecosystems via OpenClaw Security Scan, Agent Scan, Skills Scan, MCP scan, AI Infra scan and LLM jailbreak evaluation.\n\n 2733  davepoon/buildwithclaude\n         A single hub to find Claude Skills, Agents, Commands, Hooks, Plugins, and Marketplace collections to extend Claude Code, Claude Desktop, Agent SDK and OpenClaw\n\n 2513  white0dew/XiaohongshuSkills\n         支持小红书自动发布、自动评论、自动检索的 Skill。支持 OpenClaw、Codex、CC 等","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776014326395}}
{"type":"message","id":"aec48d22","parentId":"8b101d3e","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:18:56.386Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a much clearer picture. Let me focus on the most relevant ones for memory and context:\n\n**Top candidates for memory/context:**\n\n1. **volcengine/OpenViking** (22099 ⭐) - \"open-source context database designed specifically for AI Agents (such as openclaw)\" - unifies memory, resources, and skills through file system paradigm. This is a dedicated context DB, not just a skill. Could be complex to integrate.\n\n2. **MemTensor/MemOS** (8314 ⭐) - \"AI memory OS for LLM and Agent systems (moltbot, clawdbot, openclaw), enabling persistent Skill memory for cross-task skill reuse and evolution\" - This seems very relevant!\n   \n3. **sopaco/cortex-mem** (257 ⭐) - \"production-ready cognitive foundation for autonomous systems such as OpenClaw\" with memory management spanning extraction through optimization, offering SKILL, CLI, API, MCP, and dashboard - also compelling but relatively unknown.\n\n4. **CortexReach/memory-lancedb-pro-skill** (222 ⭐) - a Claude Code skill specifically for memory-lancedb-pro as a production-grade long-term memory plugin - though this leans toward the coding agent rather than OpenClaw itself.\n\nI should also check out the awesome lists since they're likely curated repositories of the best OpenClaw skills available.","thinkingSignature":"e35555d9a8456ed5feb30fcd696f683806a433a064efad1665c7481c75e455f5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xheooxyqd92t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://api.github.com/repos/volcengine/OpenViking/readme\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json, base64\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\ncontent = base64.b64decode(d['content']).decode('utf-8')\nprint(content[:3000])\n\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xheooxyqd92t_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://api.github.com/repos/MemTensor/MemOS/readme\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json, base64\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\ncontent = base64.b64decode(d['content']).decode('utf-8')\nprint(content[:3000])\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116405,"output":468,"cacheRead":15172,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132045,"cost":{"input":0.0349215,"output":0.0005616,"cacheRead":0.0009103199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03639342}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776014326405,"responseId":"062b06f687122f3d3f6368c3b80f614a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"29fdf530","parentId":"aec48d22","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:18:57.212Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xheooxyqd92t_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<div align=\"center\">\n\n<a href=\"https://openviking.ai/\" target=\"_blank\">\n  <picture>\n    <img alt=\"OpenViking\" src=\"docs/images/ov-logo.png\" width=\"200px\" height=\"auto\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n\n### OpenViking: The Context Database for AI Agents\n\nEnglish / [中文](README_CN.md) / [日本語](README_JA.md)\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openviking.ai\">Website</a> · <a href=\"https://github.com/volcengine/OpenViking\">GitHub</a> · <a href=\"https://github.com/volcengine/OpenViking/issues\">Issues</a> · <a href=\"./docs\">Docs</a>\n\n[![][release-shield]][release-link]\n[![][github-stars-shield]][github-stars-link]\n[![][github-issues-shield]][github-issues-shield-link]\n[![][github-contributors-shield]][github-contributors-link]\n[![][license-shield]][license-shield-link]\n[![][last-commit-shield]][last-commit-shield-link]\n\n👋 Join our Community\n\n📱 <a href=\"./docs/en/about/01-about-us.md#lark-group\">Lark Group</a> · <a href=\"./docs/en/about/01-about-us.md#wechat-group\">WeChat</a> · <a href=\"https://discord.com/invite/eHvx8E9XF3\">Discord</a> · <a href=\"https://x.com/openvikingai\">X</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://trendshift.io/repositories/19668\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://trendshift.io/api/badge/repositories/19668\" alt=\"volcengine%2FOpenViking | Trendshift\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 55px;\" width=\"250\" height=\"55\"/></a>\n\n</div>\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n### Challenges in Agent Development\n\nIn the AI era, data is abundant, but high-quality context is hard to come by. When building AI Agents, developers often face these challenges:\n\n- **Fragmented Context**: Memories are in code, resources are in vector databases, and skills are scattered, making them difficult to manage uniformly.\n- **Surging Context Demand**: An Agent's long-running tasks produce context at every execution. Simple truncation or compression leads to information loss.\n- **Poor Retrieval Effectiveness**: Traditional RAG uses flat storage, lacking a global view and making it difficult to understand the full context of information.\n- **Unobservable Context**: The implicit retrieval chain of traditional RAG is like a black box, making it hard to debug when errors occur.\n- **Limited Memory Iteration**: Current memory is just a record of user interactions, lacking Agent-related task memory.\n\n### The OpenViking Solution\n\n**OpenViking** is an open-source **Context Database** designed specifically for AI Agents.\n\nWe aim to define a minimalist context interaction paradigm for Agents, allowing developers to completely say goodbye to the hassle of context management. OpenViking abandons the fragmented vector storage model of traditional RAG and innovatively adopts a **\"file system paradigm\"** to unify the structured organization of memories, resources, and skills needed by Agents.\n\nWith OpenViking, developers can build an Agent's brain just like managing local files:\n\n- **Filesystem Management Paradigm** → **Solves Fragmentation**: Unified context management of memories, resources, and skills based on a filesystem paradigm.\n- **Tiered Contex"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":786,"aggregated":"<div align=\"center\">\n\n<a href=\"https://openviking.ai/\" target=\"_blank\">\n  <picture>\n    <img alt=\"OpenViking\" src=\"docs/images/ov-logo.png\" width=\"200px\" height=\"auto\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n\n### OpenViking: The Context Database for AI Agents\n\nEnglish / [中文](README_CN.md) / [日本語](README_JA.md)\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openviking.ai\">Website</a> · <a href=\"https://github.com/volcengine/OpenViking\">GitHub</a> · <a href=\"https://github.com/volcengine/OpenViking/issues\">Issues</a> · <a href=\"./docs\">Docs</a>\n\n[![][release-shield]][release-link]\n[![][github-stars-shield]][github-stars-link]\n[![][github-issues-shield]][github-issues-shield-link]\n[![][github-contributors-shield]][github-contributors-link]\n[![][license-shield]][license-shield-link]\n[![][last-commit-shield]][last-commit-shield-link]\n\n👋 Join our Community\n\n📱 <a href=\"./docs/en/about/01-about-us.md#lark-group\">Lark Group</a> · <a href=\"./docs/en/about/01-about-us.md#wechat-group\">WeChat</a> · <a href=\"https://discord.com/invite/eHvx8E9XF3\">Discord</a> · <a href=\"https://x.com/openvikingai\">X</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://trendshift.io/repositories/19668\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://trendshift.io/api/badge/repositories/19668\" alt=\"volcengine%2FOpenViking | Trendshift\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 55px;\" width=\"250\" height=\"55\"/></a>\n\n</div>\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n### Challenges in Agent Development\n\nIn the AI era, data is abundant, but high-quality context is hard to come by. When building AI Agents, developers often face these challenges:\n\n- **Fragmented Context**: Memories are in code, resources are in vector databases, and skills are scattered, making them difficult to manage uniformly.\n- **Surging Context Demand**: An Agent's long-running tasks produce context at every execution. Simple truncation or compression leads to information loss.\n- **Poor Retrieval Effectiveness**: Traditional RAG uses flat storage, lacking a global view and making it difficult to understand the full context of information.\n- **Unobservable Context**: The implicit retrieval chain of traditional RAG is like a black box, making it hard to debug when errors occur.\n- **Limited Memory Iteration**: Current memory is just a record of user interactions, lacking Agent-related task memory.\n\n### The OpenViking Solution\n\n**OpenViking** is an open-source **Context Database** designed specifically for AI Agents.\n\nWe aim to define a minimalist context interaction paradigm for Agents, allowing developers to completely say goodbye to the hassle of context management. OpenViking abandons the fragmented vector storage model of traditional RAG and innovatively adopts a **\"file system paradigm\"** to unify the structured organization of memories, resources, and skills needed by Agents.\n\nWith OpenViking, developers can build an Agent's brain just like managing local files:\n\n- **Filesystem Management Paradigm** → **Solves Fragmentation**: Unified context management of memories, resources, and skills based on a filesystem paradigm.\n- **Tiered Contex","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776014337205}}
