{"type":"message","id":"57f922f4","parentId":"a7e31c17","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:25:06.890Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know the pros and cons of continuing with the LLM Wiki system vs something else. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nLLM Wiki system pros:\n- Lightweight, file-based, no external dependencies\n- Already has 25 entity pages with substantial content\n- Schema layer (SOUL.md, AGENTS.md) already integrated\n- Knowledge compilation model is superior to RAG for recurring contexts\n- Can be queried directly by the LLM without API calls\n- Privacy-preserving (no external service)\n\nLLM Wiki system cons:\n- No automatic triggering - Ingest/Query/Lint are defined but not automated\n- Requires manual maintenance\n\n\n- Searching across the wiki is fairly manual and primitive\n- Scaling is limited since it's just files\n- No versioning or conflict resolution built in\n- Adding new documents requires a fairly complex manual process\n\nComparing to alternatives like MemOS, OpenViking, or vector search approaches: MemOS is more production-ready with automatic hierarchy and vector search, but it's heavier and requires Docker or cloud setup. OpenViking is similarly production-grade with better scalability, though it has the same dependency overhead. Vector databases like LanceDB would give better search capabilities but introduce external dependencies, whereas the lightweight file-based approach is simpler but struggles with semantic search and doesn't scale as well.\n\nThe LLM Wiki approach works well for this use case since the existing system already has entity pages built out and the Schema integration is solid. It requires some manual maintenance, but the knowledge compilation model is actually better for recurring contexts than RAG would be.","thinkingSignature":"4930d3bee1a5e0b5413c9c975d18fe162083333e7a79d9814a37799ec96bde18"},{"type":"text","text":"**LLM Wiki 体系 vs MemOS**\n\n| 维度 | LLM Wiki（现有） | MemOS |\n|------|-----------------|-------|\n| 架构 | 纯文件，无外部依赖 | 需要 Docker / LanceDB |\n| 已有内容 | 25个实体页，2311行 | 从零开始 |\n| Schema 集成 | SOUL/AGENTS 已融合 ✅ | 需单独对接 |\n| 搜索方式 | 关键词/文件名搜索 | 向量语义搜索 |\n| 自动化 | Ingest/Lint 需配置 | 开箱即用 |\n| 维护成本 | 手动定期整理 | 自动分层抽象 |\n| 启动速度 | 即时（纯文件） | 依赖服务启动 |\n| 隐私 | 完全本地 | 部分依赖外部 API |\n\n---\n\n**LLM Wiki 优点**\n\n- 轻量：零外部依赖，即开即用\n- 已有积累：25 个实体页，够用\n- Schema 层已融合：SOUL.md + AGENTS.md + entities/ 三层完整\n- 知识编译模型：优于 RAG（ recurring 场景不重复计算）\n- 完全本地：隐私无泄露风险\n- 可被 LLM 直接读取：不需要 API 调用\n\n**LLM Wiki 缺点**\n\n- 搜索原始：只能靠关键词或枚举文件名\n- 新文档 Ingest：流程定义有了，但 cron 触发还没配\n- Lint 维护：需要定期手动/半手动整理\n- 没有版本控制：多人编辑可能冲突\n- 实体页膨胀后：管理复杂度上升\n\n---\n\n**我的判断**\n\n现有 LLM Wiki 体系**够用**，但缺自动触发。MemOS 是升级方向，但现在接进来收益不大——你要重写对接，它也不比你现有体系强多少。\n\n**现阶段最优**：配齐 cron 触发，把 Ingest + Lint 自动化，剩下的等实际痛点了再升级。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13,"output":714,"cacheRead":137289,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138016,"cost":{"input":0.0000039,"output":0.0008568,"cacheRead":0.00823734,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00909804}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776014685967,"responseId":"062b085d9b8d86c607613a871295b04d"}}
