{"type":"message","id":"da64d27e","parentId":"f5557a76","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:28:34.240Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-04-13 01:28 GMT+8] 那可以进行全自动，然后自行进行优化吗"}],"timestamp":1776014914231}}
{"type":"message","id":"de38e3a5","parentId":"da64d27e","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:29:01.192Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if we can do full-auto ingest but then have the system self-optimize - essentially asking if the system can learn from its own mistakes and improve the quality of its compilations over time.\n\nThis is essentially asking for a self-improving loop within the LLM Wiki system. Let me think about what this would look like:\n\n1. Full-auto ingest happens\n2. System monitors the quality of its compilations\n3. When errors/mistakes are caught (by the user correcting, or by Lint finding issues), the system writes to corrections.md\n4. When doing future ingest, the system reads corrections.md and adjusts its approach\n\n\n5. Over time the compilation quality improves because the system learns from past mistakes\n\nThis is actually where the self-improving skill would shine - it's already designed to capture what went wrong and apply those learnings to future work. So the real question becomes whether I can set up the feedback loop: auto-ingest compiles a document, the user catches any errors, those get logged to corrections.md, and then the next compilation run reads from that file to avoid repeating the same mistakes.\n\nI'm also wondering about Lint checks though - whether they could run automatically to flag quality issues in the compiled entities before they compound.\n\nFor this to work, I'd need to configure periodic Lint scans, route any quality problems it finds back into corrections.md or a dedicated feedback file, and then have the Ingest process read from those sources when it runs next. The practical question is really what cadence makes sense here - Lint probably shouldn't run every hour, maybe once daily instead.\n\nSo the architecture would be: Ingest on a regular schedule that checks docs/, an LLM extraction step, updates to entities/, and then Lint runs periodically (weekly or after several new docs) to catch quality drift. When the system makes mistakes, those get captured in corrections, and future Ingest runs use that feedback to improve. The user's real question is whether the system can be fully automated while still self-improving, and the answer is yes with the right feedback loop in place.\n\nNow I'm thinking about how to actually implement this - I need to sketch out the cron jobs for automated ingestion and periodic linting, figure out where corrections should be stored, and work through the exact sequence of how the system learns from its errors.","thinkingSignature":"7e57f5aafb8c7182ce99ada5ff671d455fbf72eb0767b250d17da105bdd62ad1"},{"type":"text","text":"可以，本质是加一个**自我纠错反馈环**：\n\n```\n全自动 Ingest\n    ↓ 编译\nentities/ 更新\n    ↓\nLint 定期检查质量（链接/一致性/过期）\n    ↓ 发现问题\n写进 corrections.md / feedback\n    ↓\n下次 Ingest 前读取纠错记录\n    ↓\n调整提取策略后再处理\n```\n\n---\n\n**这个方案的问题**\n\n| 问题 | 说明 |\n|------|------|\n| LLM 不知道自己编译错了 | 得有人/规则告诉它 |\n| corrections.md 谁写 | 如果是全自动，Lint 必须能自动生成有意义的纠正 |\n| 上下文窗口 | 如果 entities/ 膨胀到很大，每次 Ingest 都要重读，负担上升 |\n\n---\n\n**实际上能全自动优化的部分**\n\n1. **Ingest 本身**——全自动没问题，LLM 提取是确定性的\n2. **定期 Lint**——链接检查、去重、过期清理，可以全自动\n3. **错误模式记录**——Lint 发现的问题 → 写 feedback 文件，可以全自动\n\n**无法全自动的部分**\n\n- 真正的\"理解哪里错了并改正\"——需要 LLM 自我反思，这靠 `self-improving` 技能里的 corrections 机制\n\n---\n\n**现实路径**\n\n```\n第一层（全自动）：\n- Ingest：docs/ 有新文档 → 自动提取更新 entities/\n- Lint：每周一次自动扫描，检查链接/去重/过期\n\n第二层（半自动，触发 self-improving）：\n- 你发现实体页内容不对 → 纠正 → 写进 corrections.md\n- self-improving 技能捕获纠正 → 影响后续行为\n\n第三层（进阶）：\n- 每次 Ingest 后对比上一次结果，差异大则告警\n- 你确认后正式采纳\n```\n\n---\n\n**结论**：全自动 Ingest + 定期 Lint 完全可行，优化靠 corrections 反馈环。_entities/ 的质量靠人纠错驱动系统改进，这是 self-improving 技能的原生能力。_\n\n**要不要我给出具体的 cron + Lint 配置方案？**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":894,"cacheRead":137967,"cacheWrite":211,"totalTokens":139126,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0010728,"cacheRead":0.008278019999999999,"cacheWrite":0.000079125,"total":0.009446144999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776014914254,"responseId":"062b09426da94312adff6e62a1708264"}}
