{"type":"message","id":"f3252962","parentId":"c9692719","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:33:19.765Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants automatic scoring and classification for every message. This means I need to configure the OpenClaw gateway to automatically call v8_classifier and v8_scorer on every message before responding.\n\nLooking at the document they shared earlier about the v8-router plugin, it intercepts messages via a `message_preprocess` hook and calls the v8-core service. But that's designed for port 3003 v8-core, not the current 3103/3104 setup.\n\nLet me think about what's actually available in the current setup:\n- 3104: scene classifier\n- 3103: scoring engine\n- Gateway at 3102\n\nThe question is how to integrate the classifier/scorer into the gateway's message preprocessing pipeline.\n\n\nI need to figure out whether OpenClaw's gateway actually supports plugin hooks like `message_preprocess`, and if so, how to configure it to call the existing 3103/3104 services rather than the 3003 service the v8-router was designed for. The v8-router plugin they described calls `http://localhost:3003/v1/route`, so I'd need to either adapt that to work with our current services or build a new plugin that makes the same calls to 3103 and 3104.","thinkingSignature":"47b35aa18c846c7489c23125bcbd299187c9df69291b1b520ee6273a5d1bf778"},{"type":"text","text":"好，那需要给 Gateway 配置自动评分分类的中间件。\n\n先确认一下当前 Gateway 的插件机制：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5vw4eedhj8le_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.config/systemd/user/openclaw-gateway.service 2>/dev/null | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5vw4eedhj8le_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | grep -A10 \"plugins\\|entries\\|middleware\" | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":384,"cacheRea