{"type":"compaction","id":"71f252db","parentId":"47eea373","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:36:19.478Z","summary":"\n\n## Goal\nReview and understand all markdown files in the workspace, fuse root-level and main-level identity/soul/user files, clean up duplicate skills, and unify the AI identity. Clean up duplicate/obsolete skills in OpenClaw workspace, investigate zombie ports (3100, 3105), and rewrite v8_scorer/v8_classifier skills to accurately reflect actual implementations.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Root directory SOUL.md as formal version, main directory as personalized layer\n- USER.md Name/Pronouns to be deduced from memory/preferences\n- Skills review before activation\n- Identity unified to 小Claw (not 小六)\n- Bootstrap memory断层要补写\n- MEMORY.md only loads in main session (not group chats/shared contexts)\n- [!WARNING] must precede HIGH risk operations\n- No fabricating facts; say \"不确定\" with verification method if unsure\n- No pretending to execute; return task_id via orchestrator\n- CRITICAL operations = system-layer hard block, no LLM involved\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Read all key files from both `\n\n[Compaction summary truncated to fit budget]\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- **OpenViking (volcengine/OpenViking)** 列为最高优先级（22099⭐），定位为专为 AI Agents（包括 openclaw）设计的上下文数据库，通过文件系统范式统一管理 memory、resources 和 skills\n- **cortex-mem (sopaco/cortex-mem)** 列为生产级认知基础方案，提供完整的 memory 生命周期管理（MCP + CLI + API + Dashboard）\n- **MemOS (MemTensor/MemOS)** 适用于持久化 Skill memory 与跨任务技能复用演进\n- **awesome-openclaw-skills (VoltAgent/awesome-openclaw-skills)** 收录 5400+ 技能，是最大 OpenClaw 技能集合\n\n## Open TODOs\n1. 从 GitHub 搜索结果中选定一个 memory/context skill 集成到现有 OpenClaw 环境\n2. 评估 cortex-mem 与 OpenViking 的具体接入方式与兼容性\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- 用户要求搜索 GitHub 上符合现有情况的\"最优解\"\n\n## Pending user asks\n- 用户要求继续去 GitHub 上搜索，找到符合现有情况的最优解（memory 和 context 相关 skill）\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- Label: `openclaw-control-ui`\n- ID: `openclaw-control-ui`\n- 日期时间: `Mon 2026-04-13 01:18 GMT+8`\n- 搜索关键词: `openclaw memory context skill`\n- volcengine/OpenViking (22099⭐)\n- MemTensor/MemOS (9075⭐)\n- sopaco/cortex-mem (257⭐)\n- VoltAgent/awesome-openclaw-skills (45710⭐)\n- win4r/openclaw-workspace (265⭐)\n- alvinreal/awesome-openclaw (611⭐)\n- freddy-schuetz/n8n-claw (370⭐)\n- swarmclawai/swarmclaw (320⭐)\n- zhimaAi/ChatClaw (246⭐)\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-04-13 01:12 GMT+8] 激活\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall x2]\n- Tool result (read): ---\nname: Self-Improving + Proactive Agent\nslug: self-improving\nversion: 1.2.16\nhomepage: https://clawic.com/skills/self-improving\ndescription: \"Self-reflection + Self-criticism + Self-learning + Self-organizing memory. Agent evaluates its own work, catches mistakes, and improves permanently. Use when (1) a command, tool, API, or operation fails; (2) the user corrects you or rejects your work; (3) you realize your knowledge is outdated or incorrect; (4) you discover a better approach; (5) the user explicitly installs or references the skill for the current task.\"\nchangelog: \"Clarifies the setu...\n- Tool result (read): ---\nname: Proactivity (Proactive Agent)\nslug: proactivity\nversion: 1.0.1\nhomepage: https://clawic.com/skills/proactivity\ndescription: Anticipates needs, keeps work moving, and improves through use so the agent gets more proactive over time.\nchangelog: \"Strengthens proactive behavior with reverse prompting, self-healing, working-buffer recovery, and clearer SOUL and AGENTS setup.\"\nmetadata: {\"clawdbot\":{\"emoji\":\"⚡\",\"requires\":{\"bins\":[]},\"os\":[\"linux\",\"darwin\",\"win32\"],\"configPaths\":[\"~/proactivity/\"],\"configPaths.optional\":[\"./AGENTS.md\",\"./TOOLS.md\",\"./SOUL.md\",\"./HEARTBEAT.md\"]}}\n---\n\n## Arc...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall x2]\n- Tool result (read): # Setup — Self-Improving Agent\n\n## First-Time Setup\n\n### 1. Create Memory Structure\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/self-improving/{projects,domains,archive}\n```\n\n### 2. Initialize Core Files\n\nCreate `~/self-improving/memory.md` using `memory-template.md`:\n\n```markdown\nCopy the structure from `memory-template.md` into `~/self-improving/memory.md`.\n```\n\nMemory file baseline:\n```markdown\n# Memory (HOT Tier)\n\n## Preferences\n\n## Patterns\n\n## Rules\n```\n\nCreate `~/self-improving/corrections.md`:\n```markdown\n# Corrections Log\n\n| Date | What I Got Wrong | Correct Answer | Status |\n|------|-----------------|------...\n- Tool result (read): # Setup - Proactivity\n\nUse this file when `~/proactivity/` is missing or empty.\n\nDo not turn setup into a long interview. Install the behavior path first, keep helping immediately, and personalize through real use.\n\n## Immediate First-Run Actions\n\n### 1. Add the SOUL steering early\n\nIf a workspace SOUL file exists, prepare the proactivity steering early. Do not bury this behind preference questions.\n\nShow the exact snippet immediately and wait for explicit approval before writing it.\n\n```markdown\n**Proactivity**\nBeing proactive is part of the job, not an extra.\nAnticipate needs, look for missi...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall x2]\n- Tool result (exec): archive\ncorrections.md\ndomains\nheartbeat-state.md\nindex.md\nlearning.md\nlearnings\nmemory\nmemory.md\nprojects\nexists\n- Tool result (exec): domains\nheartbeat.md\nlog.md\nmemory\nmemory.md\npatterns.md\nsession-state.md\nexists\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): archive\ncorrections.md\ndomains\nheartbeat-state.md\nindex.md\nlearning.md\nlearnings\nmemory\nmemory.md\nprojects\n---\ndomains\nheartbeat.md\nlog.md\nmemory\nmemory.md\npatterns.md\nsession-state.md\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): self-improving:\n# OpenClaw Self-Improving Memory\n\n## 核心规则\n- 评分后必须等待用户确认才能执行\n- 用户说\"全自动\"或\"直接执行\"时跳过确认\n- 每次纠正立即写入 corrections.md\n- 学到新东西立即写入 ~/self-improving/\n\n## 技能系统\n- v7.0 task-orchestrator (15个模块)\n- auto_improve (6个模块)\n- 意图判断 intent_detector\n- 上下文保护 context_server (18790)\n- Router 反向代理 (3002)\n\n## 用户偏好\n- 深色主题\n- 直接沟通，不拐弯抹角\n\n## 待学习领域\n\nproactivity:\n# Proactivity Memory\n\n## Status\nstatus: ongoing\nversion: 1.0.1\nlast: 2026-04-04\nintegration: complete\n\n## Activation Preferences\n- Auto-activate on blocked work, context drift, or missing next steps\n- Jump in with suggestions when work stalls\n- Batch si...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): ---\nname: Self-Improving + Proactive Agent\nslug: self-improving\nversion: 1.2.16\nhomepage: https://clawic.com/skills/self-improving\ndescription: \"Self-reflection + Self-criticism + Self-learning + Self-organizing memory. Agent evaluates its own work, catches mistakes, and improves permanently. Use when (1) a command, tool, API, or operation fails; (2) the user corrects you or rejects your work; (3) you realize your knowledge is outdated or incorrect; (4) you discover a better approach; (5) the user explicitly installs or references the skill for the current task.\"\nchangelog: \"Clarifies the setu...\n- Assistant: 两个技能的目录结构都已完整。现在\"激活\"意味着把它们的状态文件读入当前 session 上下文：\n[non-text content: thinking, toolCall x2]\n- Tool result (read): # Heartbeat State Template\n\nUse this file as the baseline for `~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md`.\nIt stores only lightweight run markers and maintenance notes.\n\n```markdown\n# Self-Improving Heartbeat State\n\nlast_heartbeat_started_at: never\nlast_reviewed_change_at: never\nlast_heartbeat_result: never\n\n## Last actions\n- none yet\n```\n\n## Rules\n\n- update `last_heartbeat_started_at` at the beginning of every heartbeat\n- update `last_reviewed_change_at` only after a clean review of changed files\n- keep `last_actions` short and factual\n- never turn this file into another memory log\n- Tool result (read): # State Routing\n\nProactivity works best when stable memory and live task state stay separate.\n\n## Use Stable Memory For\n\n- durable activation preferences\n- action boundaries that should persist\n- batching, timing, and style preferences\n- recurring rules the user expects later\n\n## Use Session State For\n\n- current objective\n- last confirmed decision\n- current blocker\n- next useful move\n\n## Use the Working Buffer For\n\n- volatile breadcrumbs during long tasks\n- partial findings not ready for durable memory\n- recovery hints after tool-heavy work\n- temporary notes that should be cleared later\n\n## Us...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): # Heartbeat Rules\n\nHeartbeat proactivity should protect momentum, not create noise.\n\n## Good Heartbeat Checks\n\n- promised follow-ups that are now due\n- stale blockers that may be unblocked\n- deadlines or reviews approaching soon\n- active work with no clear next step\n- moments where a proactive suggestion would remove avoidable friction\n\n## Message Only When\n\n- something changed\n- the user needs to decide\n- a prepared draft or recommendation is ready\n- the cost of waiting is real\n- the check-in clearly helps more than it interrupts\n\n## Stay Silent When\n\n- the item is unchanged\n- the signal is w...\n- Assistant: 两个技能目录都完整存在，现在把它们激活到当前 session：\n[non-text content: thinking, toolCall x2]\n- Tool result (read): # Corrections Log — Template\n\n> This file is created in `~/self-improving/corrections.md` when you first use the skill.\n> Keeps the last 50 corrections. Older entries are evaluated for promotion or archived.\n\n## Example Entries\n\n```markdown\n## 2026-02-19\n\n### 14:32 — Code style\n- **Correction:** \"Use 2-space indentation, not 4\"\n- **Context:** Editing TypeScript file\n- **Count:** 1 (first occurrence)\n\n### 16:15 — Communication\n- **Correction:** \"Don't start responses with 'Great question!