{"type":"message","id":"7963c5b6","parentId":"d28a23a6","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:40:24.547Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The hook is enabled. Now I need to restart the gateway for the hook to take effect. But first, let me also write the second part - modifying the agent bootstrap to read the context.json file.\n\nActually, before restarting the gateway, let me also set up the agent-side reading. I need to update the bootstrap/continuousity section to read the context.json file.\n\nBut actually, let me think about this more carefully. The hook writes to `~/.openclaw/sessions/{sessionKey}/context.json`. When the agent bootstraps for the current session, it needs to read this file.\n\nThe bootstrap happens in the agent's startup phase. Looking at AGENTS.md, the bootstrap sequence is:\n\n\n1. Read SOUL.md\n2. Read USER.md\n3. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today + yesterday)\n4. If in MAIN SESSION: also read MEMORY.md\n\nSo where in this sequence would the context.json file be read? I think the cleanest approach is to update the AGENTS.md bootstrap sequence to add a step for reading the context.json file after the memory files. This way the agent has all the session context available when it starts processing.\n\nLet me draft the update to AGENTS.md to include reading `~/.openclaw/sessions/{currentSessionKey}/context.json` if it exists.","thinkingSignature":"de3a8e6029eddf6ca37539eb53e4ebe2dd76a5086d0e04a9c390f73701dd691e"},{"type":"text","text":"Hook 已启用 ✅ 需要重启 Gateway 使其生效。\n\n同时写第二部分——让 agent 在 bootstrap 时读入 context.json：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s1ky57hpsis7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/AGENTS.md","limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35112,"output":345,"cacheRead":17719,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53176,"cost":{"input":0.010533599999999999,"output":0.000414,"cacheRead":0.00106314,"cacheWrite":0,"tot