{"type":"message","id":"1db0d1fd","parentId":"8d9641f4","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:40:46.471Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to restart the gateway for the hook to take effect. But let me also check - when the user sends a message, the hook fires and writes to context.json. Then the agent bootstraps and reads context.json. But there's a timing issue - the hook fires before the agent processes the message, so the agent should read the correct context.json.\n\nHowever, there's another issue: the agent bootstraps at the start of the session, not at every message. So the context.json that was written by the hook for the previous message will be read by the agent on the NEXT message (or on session start).\n\nWait, let me think again:\n1. User sends message A\n2. Gateway receives message A\n3. Hook fires (message:preprocessed) → writes context.json for message A\n\n\n4. Agent bootstraps for message A → reads context.json (from message A's hook result, or empty if first message)\n5. Agent processes and responds to message A\n6. User sends message B\n7. Hook fires → writes context.json for message B\n8. Agent bootstraps for message B → reads context.json from message B\n9. Agent processes and responds\n\nThis flow actually works perfectly - the agent bootstraps on each message and reads the context that was written by the hook firing on that same message.\n\nNow I need to restart the gateway to get the hook working, and I should verify that reading context.json is included in the agent's bootstrap context since the hook stores the data in the session directory.","thinkingSignature":"a79f168c4d06527573474cd678bcd2a2b709fc3bbf452c64c71f5c6be92e0d6a"},{"type":"text","text":"现在重启 Gateway 让 hook 生效：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_htjwqxaq3psq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw gateway restart 2>/dev/null; echo \"restarting...\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messag