{"type":"message","id":"2ec6acb1","parentId":"50595166","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:49:47.014Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The current model is `paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2`. This is a relatively small model (384-dim embeddings).\n\nOptions for a better model:\n\n1. **`paraphrase-multilingual-mpnet-base-v2`** - Same multilingual coverage but much better quality (768-dim, larger model). Compatible replacement, same API.\n\n2. **`text2vec-base-chinese`** - Chinese-specific model, best for Chinese but only Chinese.\n\n3. **`m3e-base`** - Chinese-specific, good quality, open source.\n\n4. **`bge-m3`** or **`bge-base-zh`** - Chinese-specific, often considered state-of-art for Chinese.\n\n\nFor a multilingual setup, `paraphrase-multilingual-mpnet-base-v2` would be the straightforward upgrade since it maintains the same multilingual capabilities while improving performance. Though if the use case is primarily Chinese, then `text2vec-base-chinese` or `bge-base-zh` would be stronger choices. The tricky part is that the training data uses specific trigger words like 重构 and 分析, so even with a better model, I might hit similar limitations depending on what phrases are actually in that dataset.","thinkingSignature":"14f4f06e4b254d4977091e534eae7888a4f9490a249c954266a314537c81427b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zumr5zncc2a9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/ai/openclaw-classifier -name \"*.py\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"training_data\\|synthetic\\|scene_label\\|training\" 2>/dev/null | head -5","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47458,"output":328,"cacheRead":17776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65562,"cost":{"input":0.014237399999999999,"output":0.00039359999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0010665599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01569756}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776016177013,"responseId":"062b0e30f1a5950904021f5b81b79a5