{"type":"message","id":"9af69565","parentId":"9ca6394a","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:50:48.061Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at app.py to understand how the classifier is initialized and how to restart the service.","thinkingSignature":"aa6e5bfc813c24d626d9d2f3d22481eb50e3a94fa1310559f3da3b45b8f6f02f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zc52qx3kbwbf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/openclaw-classifier/python-service/app.py 2>/dev/null","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49179,"output":73,"cacheRead":17776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67028,"cost":{"input":0.0147537,"output":0.0000876,"cacheRead":0.0010665599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01590786}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776016245616,"responseId":"062b0e75d46f82364dd495757c035141"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0db70e81","parentId":"9af69565","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:50:48.139Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zc52qx3kbwbf_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nPython 分类服务 - Flask API\n启动: python app.py\n端口: 5000\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport json\n\nos.environ['HF_ENDPOINT'] = 'https://hf-mirror.com'\n\nfrom flask import Flask, request, jsonify\nfrom classifier.scene_classifier import SceneClassifier\n\n# 加载分类器\nclassifier = None\ntry:\n    classifier = SceneClassifier.load(\"models/scene_classifier.pkl\")\n    print(\"Loaded embedding classifier\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Embedding classifier unavailable: {e}\")\n    from classifier.rule_classifier import RuleClassifier\n    classifier = RuleClassifier()\n    print(\"Using rule-based fallback classifier\")\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n@app.route(\"/classify\", methods=[\"POST\"])\ndef classify():\n    try:\n        data = request.get_json()\n        text = data.get(\"text\", \"\")\n        if not text:\n            return jsonify({\"error\": \"text is required\"}), 400\n        \n        result = classifier.predict(text)\n        return jsonify(result)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return jsonify({\n            \"label\": \"default\",\n            \"confidence\": 0.0,\n            \"meta\": \"error\",\n            \"error\": str(e)\n        }), 200\n\n@app.route(\"/health\", methods=[\"GET\"])\ndef health():\n    return jsonify({\"status\": \"ok\", \"classifier\": \"loaded\"})\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=5000, debug=False)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":44,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nPython 分类服务 - Flask API\n启动: python app.py\n端口: 5000\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport json\n\nos.environ['HF_ENDPOINT'] = 'https://hf-mirror.com'\n\nfrom flask import Flask, request, jsonify\nfrom classifier.scene_classifier import SceneClassifier\n\n# 加载分类器\nclassifier = None\ntry:\n    classifier = SceneClassifier.load(\"models/scene_classifier.pkl\")\n    print(\"Loaded embedding classifier\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Embedding classifier unavailable: {e}\")\n    from classifier.rule_classifier import RuleClassifier\n    classifier = RuleClassifier()\n    print(\"Using rule-based fallback classifier\")\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n@app.route(\"/classify\", methods=[\"POST\"])\ndef classify():\n    try:\n        data = request.get_json()\n        text = data.get(\"text\", \"\")\n        if not text:\n            return jsonify({\"error\": \"text is required\"}), 400\n        \n        result = classifier.predict(text)\n        return jsonify(result)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return jsonify({\n            \"label\": \"default\",\n            \"confidence\": 0.0,\n            \"meta\": \"error\",\n            \"error\": str(e)\n        }), 200\n\n@app.route(\"/health\", methods=[\"GET\"])\ndef health():\n    return jsonify({\"status\": \"ok\", \"classifier\": \"loaded\"})\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=5000, debug=False)","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776016248130}}
{"type":"message","id":"04b84c8b","parentId":"0db70e81","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:50:57.534Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup:\n1. The service is Flask on port 5000, but we access it via 3104 (probably a reverse proxy via pt_main_thread)\n2. The classifier is loaded from `models/scene_classifier.pkl`\n3. If loading fails, it falls back to `RuleClassifier`\n\nThe key insight: the model is saved in a pickle file `models/scene_classifier.pkl`. The `SceneClassifier.load()` method loads the encoder via `_load_encoder()` which calls `SentenceTransformer(self.model_name)`. \n\nSo when I change the model name in `scene_classifier.py` and retrain (or just re-initialize), it will download the new model and save the embeddings.\n \nI need to trace how port 3104 connects to this Flask service—it's likely proxied through the `pt_main_thread` process. The training happens separately through a script that loads the multilingual model, generates embeddings from the training data, fits a KNN classifier, and persists everything to the pickle file.\n\nOnce I update the model name to `paraphrase-multilingual-mpnet-base-v2`, I can run the training script to generate new embeddings and save them. The Flask service should then pick up the updated model on its next restart. I should also check what the training script looks like to understand the full workflow.","thinkingSignature":"3af327f4dc8941c8762de457fd1248eaaf9ac42c2f32a327edb44888b4cb5d08"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_48sxciv7r1j9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/ai/openclaw-classifier -name \"*.py\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v __pycache__ | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49591,"output":343,"cacheRead":17776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67710,"cost":{"input":0.0148773,"output":0.0004116,"cacheRead":0.0010665599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01635546}},"stop