{"type":"message","id":"c8fb0266","parentId":"7aa17df4","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:53:21.140Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still problematic. The model is very confident but giving None for many inputs. This is strange. Let me look at the predict function more carefully.\n\nThe predict function returns None when:\n1. `top_conf < self.confidence_threshold` (0.5)\n2. `len(weights) >= 2 and (weights[0] - weights[1]) < self.ambiguity_gap` (0.1)\n\nFor \"搭建docker环境\" to return None with confidence 1.00, it must be hitting the second condition (ambiguous) - meaning the top 2 candidates have very similar weights.\n\nThe problem is that \"搭建docker环境\" could match both \"task_multi_step\" (搭建一个完整的 React 项目) and \"vague_request\" (Docker) - making it ambiguous.\n\n\nI need to verify the model's actual output, including the confidence scores and candidates it's considering, to understand why it's being flagged as ambiguous.","thinkingSignature":"ed1fd67dc2d0759d52bcffbdf3943fcc804e6dd2b4504a46bbaebd76151f3722"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cs3sd4kfwx59_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ai/openclaw-classifier/python-service && python3 -c \"\nimport os\nos.environ['HF_ENDPOINT'] = 'https://hf-mirror.com'\nfrom classifier.scene_classifier import SceneClassifier\n\nclf = SceneClassifier.load('models/scene_classifier.pkl')\n\ntests = ['搭建docker环境', '安装docker', 'docker环境搭建']\nfor t in tests:\n    r = clf.predict(t)\n    print(f'Input: {t}')\n    print(f'  Result: {r}')\n    print()\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54845,"output":340,"cacheRead":17776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72961,"cost":{"input":0.0164535,"output":0.000408,"cacheRead":0.0010665599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01792806}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776016392979,"responseId":"062b0f096dac1745f9396c9d6cf95ee4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"81921c68","parentId":"c8fb0266","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:53:31.021Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cs3sd4kfwx59_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Input: 搭建docker环境\n  Result: {'label': None, 'confidence': 0.9999997615814209, 'meta': 'ambiguous', 'top_candidates': [('task_multi_step', 0.9999997615814209), ('task_multi_step', 0.9473062753677368)]}\n\nInput: 安装docker\n  Result: {'label': 'task_multi_step', 'confidence': 1.0, 'meta': 'confident', 'top_candidates': [('task_multi_step', 1.0), ('task_multi_step', 0.8028436899185181)]}\n\nInput: docker环境搭建\n  Result: {'label': None, 'confidence': 0.9999998807907104, 'meta': 'ambiguous', 'top_candidates': [('task_multi_step', 0.9999998807907104), ('task_multi_step', 0.9473063349723816)]}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9779,"aggregated":"Input: 搭建docker环境\n  Result: {'label': None, 'confidence': 0.9999997615814209, 'meta': 'ambiguous', 'top_candidates': [('task_multi_step', 0.9999997615814209), ('task_multi_step', 0.9473062753677368)]}\n\nInput: 安装docker\n  Result: {'label': 'task_multi_step', 'confidence': 1.0, 'meta': 'confident', 'top_candidates': [('task_multi_step', 1.0), ('task_multi_step', 0.8028436899185181)]}\n\nInput: docker环境搭建\n  Result: {'label': None, 'confidence': 0.9999998807907104, 'meta': 'ambiguous', 'top_candidates': [('task_multi_step', 0.9999998807907104), ('task_multi_step', 0.9473063349723816)]}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776016410999}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a70286a","parentId":"81921c68","timestamp":"2026-04-12T17:53:42.073Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the real problem! The `top_candidates` are returning the **same label twice** - both candidates are `task_multi_step`. This means the KNN is finding the same label for both neighbors, but with different distances. This happens because:\n\n1. The KNN has `n_neighbors=3` but there are only 9 classes\n2. The 3 nearest neighbors all happen to be of the same class `task_multi_step`\n3. The ambiguity check `weights[0] - weights[1] < 0.1` is triggered because both weights are very close (0.99 vs 0.94)\n\nWait, looking more carefully:- top1: task_multi_step (0.9999)\n- top2: task_multi_step (0.9473) - SAME LABEL!\n\nThis is a bug in the predict function - it should deduplicate candidates by label. The `ambiguity_gap` check is comparing weights of the same class, which doesn't make sense.\n\n\nThe fix is to deduplicate the candidates by label before applying the ambiguity check, so I'm not comparing weights from the same class. The confidence_threshold check should also be applied after deduplication to get the actual top candidate's weight.","thinkingSignature":"e1b7d5b9b7523f1ba3fbfe8ac93be22542c2a580a7ad71aad9a7c65eafb85d3b"},{"type":"text","text":"找到根本问题了——KNN 的 3 个近邻命中了**同一个标签**（`task_multi_step`），导致 `top_candidates` 里两个候选是同一个类，触发了误判。\n\n这是个代码 bug，需要修复 `predict` 函数：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_td2hxf2rr11s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/openclaw-classifier/python-service/classifier/scene_classifier.py","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55406,"output":359,"cacheRead":17776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73541,"cost":{"input":0.0166218,"output":0.00043079999999999995,"cacheRead":0.0010665599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01811916}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776016411024,"responseId