{"type":"message","id":"069083cc","parentId":"0b79edf6","timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:03:02.103Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The systemd service is active and running, and it's the one that's on port 3104. The service file I updated points to `/usr/bin/python3 /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/api_server.py` but it fails to bind because there's already something on port 3104.Wait, the service says it's active and running but the log shows it failed to bind. So it's NOT on port 3104. But `ss` shows something IS on port 3104 with pid 287663.\n\nWait - the service PID is 287855 and it failed to bind. But ss shows pid 287663. There might be a race condition. Or maybe the service started successfully and something else is also running.\n\nLet me just stop the systemd service and see what happens. Since I updated the service file to use `/usr/bin/python3 api_server.py`, the old venv-based binary is gone. But the service is still running the old venv-based python. Wait - no, I changed the ExecStart to use `/usr/bin/python3`. But systemctl daemon-reload was run. Let me check if the service picked up the new config.\n\nActually, looking at the service status - it says \"Active: active (running) since Mon 2026-04-13 02:02:38\" and \"Main PID: 287855\". And the error is from Apr 13 02:02:45. So it started at 02:02:38 but the binding failed at 02:02:45? That doesn't make sense - if binding failed, the service should have exited. Unless there's another process that took the port between the failed bind and the service restart.\n\nWait - let me re-read. The service started at 02:02:38, then at 02:02:45 the python process logged the bind error. But port 3104 IS bound. Something is very off here. Let me just kill everything and start fresh. But I can't disable the systemd service because I need it to keep the classifier running.\n\nActually, looking at the systemctl output more carefully - the service is \"active (running)\" but the py