{"type":"message","id":"789c601c","parentId":"647722e3","timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:03:18.246Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK port 3104 is finally free. Now let me update the Flask app to use port 3104 and start it, OR update the v8 api_server.py to use the new scene_classifier.py.Actually, the simplest thing is to use the v8 api_server.py (which is what the service is configured to run) but with the new model. I already copied the model. The issue is that the v8 api_server.py fails to load the classify endpoint.Let me re-examine the v8 api_server.py. The pipeline works when I test it directly. But the FastAPI endpoint returns 500. This is very strange.\n\nWait - let me look at the api_server.py again. The module-level code that runs on import might be failing silently. Let me check if there's a difference between the api_server.py imports and what I tested directly.Actually, let me look at what happens when the api_server.py runs. On import, it:1. \n\nSets up the environment, imports FastAPI and the orchestrator, then instantiates both at module level. When a /classify request comes in, it should call pipeline.process(text). My direct test of the pipeline worked fine, so the issue must be something specific to how the FastAPI server is running or how requests are being handled.","thinkingSignature":"a6dc89a3755ba5287d932b18810f9d18f346f41e81558f01e86a3de9e0e5beeb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p7s7nita6dxq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/api_server.py 2>/dev/null | sed -n '1,60p'","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":77870,"output":333,"cacheRead":17776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95979,"cost":{"input":0.023361,"output":0.00039959999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0010665599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02482716}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776016989704,"responseId":"062b115de4cb09e083f24b