{"type":"message","id":"537492fd","parentId":"fb83ccbd","timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:34:35.719Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants a comprehensive, strict review of the overall framework. Let me think about what we have built and what's still missing or problematic.\n\n**Current state of the system:**\n\n1. **Hook system**: We have 7 hooks running:\n   - boot-md\n   - bootstrap-extra-files\n   - command-logger\n   - session-memory\n   - memory-core-short-term-dreaming-cron\n   - auto-score-classify\n   - session-summary\n\n2. **Services**:\n   - Gateway (3102)\n   - v8_scorer (3103)\n   - v8_classifier (3104)\n   - scene-classifier (3105)\n   - Context API (3106)\n\n3. **Skills**:\n   - self-improving (active)\n   - proactivity (active)\n   - elite-longterm-memory\n   - memory-keeper\n   - v8_scorer\n   - v8_classifier\n\n4. **Memory system**:\n   - memory/ daily logs\n   - MEMORY.md\n   - entities/ (LLM Wiki)\n   - docs/ (empty)\n   - session summaries (now being generated)\n\nI'm spotting some critical gaps. There are duplicate classifier services running on 3104 and 3105 with conflicting implementations, the LLM Wiki system has no actual documents feeding into it, and there's no enforced budget management for context. Additionally, the session summaries we've built aren't being actively integrated back into the Wiki knowledge base, and I haven't validated whether the auto-score-classify hook is actually triggering properly or if the bootstrap process correctly reads those context files. I should also verify whether the skill configurations for proactivity and self-improvement are genuinely compatible with the current hook and agent architecture.","thinkingSignature":"594c516726ea6c794813b66e5a97c3f90123da2400c6b7bd439325d6720a3f7f"},{"type":"text","text":"逐层严格评审：\n\n---\n\n**第一层：端口与服务**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bvt2b9as9lrs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp | grep -E \"310[0-9]|3