{"type":"message","id":"99e38af4","parentId":"83f08010","timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:35:27.798Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"- **3106**: openclaw-listener (pid 597) — this is the Feishu/workspace listener\n- **3100**: The process that owns it isn't found by lsof (pid not returned) — this is very suspicious. It could be a process that's already exited but the port is still held (TIME_WAIT), OR it could be a kernel-level listener.\n\nWait, `ss -tlnp` shows 3100 listening but `lsof -i :3100` returns nothing. This means either:\n1. The process exited but the socket wasn't properly closed\n2. It's a kernel-level listener (unlikely for TCP)","thinkingSignature":"f7d6f116738a914e624b5437f79c561c38e199c5cfaad8b1dae417093617abcd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4va10g9oz3ez_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | grep 3100","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4va10g9oz3ez_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /proc/net/tcp 2>/dev/null | awk 'NR>1 {print $2, $4}' | while read local state; do echo \"$local $state\" | awk '{print $1}' | xargs -I{} printf '%d\\n' 0x{} 2>/dev/null; done | grep \"3100\\|3105\" || echo \"checking...\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":101289,"output":292,"cacheRead":17846,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119427,"cost":{"input":0.0303867,"output":0.0003504,"cacheRead":0.0010707599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03180786}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776018918808,"responseId":"062b18e68303c8da1b82e233a7a1b075"}}
