{"type":"message","id":"26780dfe","parentId":"6bb3d2d8","timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:36:17.714Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the hooks/handler.js and also understand if there's a mechanism for the agent to read context.json during bootstrap.\n\nThe key question: when the agent bootstraps, does it actually run code that reads context.json? Or is AGENTS.md just a set of instructions that I (the LLM) am supposed to follow, meaning I read it myself?\n\nLooking at the AGENTS.md file — it's instructions for me (the AI agent). So when I'm bootstrapped, I should read the AGENTS.md file and follow its instructions, which includes reading context.json.\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. User sends message\n2. Hook fires → writes context.json\n3. Agent bootstraps → reads AGENTS.md → follows instructions → reads context.json and session summary\n\n\n4. Agent responds\n\nThis means the current implementation should work, but only for subsequent messages in the session since the hook runs before my bootstrap on the first message. On the very first message, there's no prior context.json yet. But looking more carefully at the event timing: `message:preprocessed` fires after media processing but before agent bootstrap, so when I respond to message N, context.json contains data from message N-1, which is actually sufficient for providing analysis of the current message.\n\nThe system prompt notes that for session continuity I should read recent session summaries from memory, which is what the session-summary hook generates. This approach should work. However, I need to address several critical issues: 3100 is a zombie port, 3105 is down and needs investigation, and I should verify whether session summaries are being created correctly. I also need to examine how session-summary interacts with session-memory since both hooks fire on /new and /reset commands, and running them sequentially could cause problems.","thinkingSignature":"2d276eb55042