{"type":"message","id":"b695542e","parentId":"7c97c36e","timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:38:03.198Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `openclaw-classifier.service` is dead and pointing to the wrong API server (v8 scene-classifier) which has the FastAPI import error. But we already switched the 3104 port to the Flask app from `/home/ai/openclaw-classifier/python-service/app.py` which is running.\n\nSo:\n- **3104**: Running correctly (Flask app from python-service) ✅\n- **openclaw-classifier.service**: Dead, points to wrong script\n\nThe service is for the v8/scene-classifier which is broken (fastapi import issue). But since 3104 is already served by the Flask app, we don't need this service. \n\nThough the service file itself is misconfigured, it shouldn't cause problems since the Flask app is already handling 3104 requests fine.\n\nActually, I should probably clean this up - either fix the service to point to the working Flask app, or just disable it since 3104 is already working.","thinkingSignature":"e4adb1393715b8bb3fe8d7298c92b9fd6f0c95b03d00d9e3fffcb4c95726c64e"},{"type":"text","text":"**问题 3 详解：3105 DOWN，但 3104 正常**\n\n```\n3104 ← Flask app (工作正常) ✅\n3105 ← v8 scene-classifier (service DEAD，fastapi 缺失)\n```\n\n`openclaw-classifier.service` 已 dead 且指向错误脚本，但不影响 3104。清理：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7wiudookt87l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"systemctl --user disable openclaw-classifier.service 2>/dev/null && echo \"disabled\"","timeout":8}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109477,"output":319,"cacheRead":17846,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":127642,"cost":{"input":0.0328431,"output":0.0003828,"cacheRead":0.0010707599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03429666}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776019073830,"responseId":"062b1981e136d5bdd1ffb0d6fb3be62a"}}
