{"type":"message","id":"0bddad06","parentId":"94f70ef9","timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:49:00.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to go step by step, thinking at each step. Let me start with Step 1: Verify session-summary can generate a summary.\n\nLet me think step by step:\n\n**Step 1: Test session-summary generation**\n\nI need to trigger /new or /reset to test if the hook actually fires and generates a summary. I can do this via the OpenClaw CLI or by sending a command.\n\nBut wait - I can't just \"send /new\" through a tool. I need to use the OpenClaw CLI or RPC to trigger it.\n\nLet me think about how to test this. The session-summary hook listens for `command:new` or `command:reset` events. \n\nI could trigger a `/new` command directly through the gateway RPC, or maybe check if there's a command-line interface for this. Let me first verify what session data is actually available to the hook - specifically, whether `context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile` contains the right information when the hook fires. Looking at the session-memory hook logic, it appears to construct session paths based on the agent ID and request key, then searches for `.jsonl` files in the sessions directory, though I'm not seeing those files in `~/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/` where I'd expect them. The hook actually reads from the session file path provided in the event context itself—whether that's from `previousSessionEntry` or `sessionEntry`. So for my session-summary hook to work, I need to figure out what session file path the gateway will actually pass in the event when /new is triggered, since that's what determines whether we're reading the right conversation history. I need to actually trigger /new to see what the gateway passes in the event context, since I can't determine the session file path from static analysis alone.","thinkingSignature":"1e4b36af92892068a4f86554480070855563858cbb54beafe69258f116cf896c"},{"type":"text","text":"好，Step 1 开始。\n\n---\n\n**Step 1：验证 session-summary 是否能生成摘要**\n\n触发 `/new` 命令，看 hook 是否生成摘要文件。\n\n但我需要先确认一件事——发 `/new` 时，gateway 会传递什么 sessionFile 路径？\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dr14i90kp5nq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw --help 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"new\\|reset\\|command\" | head -10","timeout":8}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":493,"cacheRead":130909,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131402,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0.0005916,"cacheRead":0.00785454,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00844614}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776019725821,"responseId":"062b1c0d45c4a63f07b53cf581456b1b"}}
