{"type":"message","id":"e642f2ac","parentId":"3f5ac85a","timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:49:14.723Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see there's a `reset` command. But there's no `new` command in the CLI. The `/new` command is a session-level command that gets processed by the gateway, not a CLI command.\n\nLet me think about how to trigger /new. The web chat UI probably has a button for this. But I can't access the UI.\n\nActually, wait - I can send a message that triggers the gateway's session management. Or maybe I can look at how the gateway handles /new commands.\n\nActually, looking at the hooks docs earlier - `command:new` fires when `/new` command is issued. This is a message-level command that the gateway processes.\n\nI wonder if I can just send a `/new` message through the normal message channel (webchat) and it would work. But since this is the webchat session, I can't easily test it without potentially disrupting the current conversation.\n \nWait, I should check the session-keys for this conversation. The current session is `agent:main:main` - when I send `/new`, it would create a new session, but I'd lose this conversation context and the user might not even see the new session interface in webchat mode.\n\nLet me try a different approach instead. I could look at the cron job runs to understand what a `/new` command actually produces, or I could create a temporary test session to see if the hook fires without risking the main conversation. Actually, I'm realizing the safest move is to just send `/new` as a message and observe what happens through the system events - the hook should fire and create a summary before the session resets, and since the context already shows this came from the webchat UI, I should be able to track the effects.","thinkingSignature":"0b9f6f4d3be71c01c6e4f97a4909dbd13b33417f995f8cac9a2e70cb50412791"},{"type":"text","text":"`/new` 是 gateway 消息命令，不是 CLI 命令。我需要通过消息触发。\n\n让我通过 RPC 直接向 gateway 发命令：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vv823raqqbmw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:3102/rpc 2>/dev/null | head -3; echo \"---\"; curl -s http://127.0.0.1:3102/api/status 2>/dev/null | head -5","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vv823raqqbmw_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions -name \"*.jsonl\" -mmin -60 2>/dev/null | head -3","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":113686,"output":530,"cacheRead":17846,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132062,"cost":{"input":0.0341058,"output":0.000636,"cacheRead":0.0010707599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03581255999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776019740832,"responseId":"062b1c1c8260b841b8fb6aa59e75d75e"}}
