{"type":"message","id":"38b642f2","parentId":"f5406ba5","timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:49:39.969Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The current session file is at `2d625705-5c75-484e-bcf0-29f5034c6b20.jsonl` - 1.9MB, just modified. This is the session that would be summarized when /new is triggered.\n\nNow I should proceed to let the user trigger /new. But wait - I need to think about whether there's a way to test without disrupting. Actually, the session-summary hook runs asynchronously (fire-and-forget), so even if the session resets, the hook's writeSummaryFile() would still complete in the background.\n\nLet me verify this by checking if writeSummaryFile is truly fire-and-forget in the handler... Yes, it is:```javascript\nwriteSummaryFile(summary, date, time, event.sessionKey).catch((err) => {  console.error(\"[session-summary] Write error:\", err);});\n\n\n```\n\nThis is called without `await`, so it runs in the background. After /new, the new session would start and the old session's summary would have been written.\n\nOK so my plan is: Ask user to trigger /new → I check memory/ for new summary file. But actually, I'm overthinking this. The user is right here and can just trigger /new right now. Let me ask them to do it.","thinkingSignature":"ba629a5435c133e380cea8981e065bedaca03a6e5dd441b47f5fec12101a5d0f"},{"type":"text","text":"当前 session 文件已确认：`2d625705-5c75-484e-bcf0-29f5034c6b20.jsonl`（1.9MB，持续写入中）\n\n---\n\n**Step 1 现在执行**：请发 `/new` 命令。\n\n发完后我来检查：\n1. `memory/` 是否有新的 `<!-- summary-only -->` 摘要文件\n2. 新 session 是否正常启动\n\n你发 `/new`，我来验证结果。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":115019,"output":369,"cacheRead":17846,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133234,"cost":{"input":0.0345057,"output":0.0004428,"cacheRead":0.0010707599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03601926}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776019769254,"responseId":"062b1c3864a111840b08cf78416af965"}}
